President Buhari Safe The Defense Headquarters has reported that no death news has been recorded so far since the abduction of over 300 students of Government Science Secondary School in Kankara Katsina state after gunmen attacked the school.  The Coordinator Defense Media Operations Maj. Gen. John Enenche who made this known while briefing newsmen on the routine military operations across the country and its efforts towards rescuing the kidnapped school children today in Abuja, assured that the military is taking all possible steps on its kinetic and surveillance operations to make sure the children are not harmed. Major General Enenche also disclosed that President Muhammadu Buhari's safety is not threatened in any way in Katsina State.  On the resurgence of COVID 19 amongst senior military officers, he said measures are been made to make sure military personnel get tested across theaters of operations,military offices and barracks amongst others. Our correspondent report that on the 3 December 2020, troops of 32 Artillery Brigade in conjunction with personnel of the Nigerian Police Force, NSCDC And NDLEA arrested 2 suspected drug  peddlers with 59 bags of Indian Hemp along Ala road in Akure South Local Government Area of Ondo State.